comment: Global offset is -1.5 to compensate glass-supported homing procedure. Printing of only first layer of GelMA with 1x construct = test print to check on offset. Vol. T1: 200 µL (layer 1). Construct looking well-defined and with correct height.
next steps: Clean of ink vat 1 with DPBS (under hood). Continue with bioprinting 6x constructs.

comment: Global offset is -1.5 to compensate glass-supported homing procedure. MSCs (donor 953) in GelMA (T1) and HUVECs in HAMA (T2). Vol. T1: 600 µL (layer 1), + 400 µL (layer 3). Vol. T2: 600 µL (layer 2). Washing channels: dipping, then rinsing 3x1 mL warm DPBS with pipette, removing excess liquid with KimWipe (NOT touching channels). Despite some bubbles and one missing channel corner on one print, constructs look fine. All collected in separate 24-ULA-wells with 0.5 mL 2x Hase in ECGM2 +P/S.
next steps: Cleaning of both ink vats with soap water/DI water/80% EtOH. Repeat print with MSC donor 923.
